---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Claude Code Privacy: Stop Leaking Source Code, Secrets, and PII"
  description="Learn how Claude Code sends your code to Anthropic's API and how to protect it. Install a local privacy proxy in 30 seconds to mask API keys, database credentials, and sensitive data before they leave your machine."
  keywords="Claude Code隐私,保护代码不被AI读取,Claude代码安全,Anthropic API安全,AI编程工具数据防护"
  canonicalURL="https://privacygw.pages.dev/protect-claude-code-privacy"
  ogType="article">
  <Nav />

  <section class="seo-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="seo-header">
        <div class="seo-badge">Claude Code Privacy Guide</div>
        <h1>Claude Code Privacy: Stop Leaking Source Code and Secrets</h1>
        <p class="seo-subtitle">
          Claude Code is a powerful AI coding assistant that runs in your terminal. But every prompt
          you type — every file you reference, every secret in your env — gets sent to Anthropic's
          API. Here is how to keep your sensitive data under your control.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-tldr glass">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> Claude Code sends your terminal context — including environment
        variables, code snippets, and file contents — to Anthropic's API. Use AI Privacy Gateway as
        a local proxy to automatically mask API keys, passwords, PII, and other sensitive data
        before they reach Anthropic. One environment variable change. 30 seconds.
      </div>

      <h2>What Data Does Claude Code Send?</h2>
      <p>
        When you use Claude Code, the CLI tool sends several types of data to Anthropic's API:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Code and file contents</strong> from your current project</li>
        <li><strong>Environment variables</strong> that could contain API keys and secrets</li>
        <li><strong>Terminal output</strong> that may include sensitive command results</li>
        <li><strong>Git history</strong> including commit messages with potential credential references</li>
        <li><strong>Configuration files</strong> (.env, config files) referenced in your prompts</li>
        <li><strong>Internal business logic</strong> and proprietary algorithms</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        While Anthropic has strict data handling policies, the safest approach is to ensure
        sensitive data never leaves your machine in plain text. A local privacy proxy is the
        most effective way to achieve this.
      </p>

      <h2>How AI Privacy Gateway Protects Claude Code</h2>
      <p>
        AI Privacy Gateway sits between Claude Code and Anthropic's API. It scans every outgoing
        request for sensitive patterns — API keys, passwords, phone numbers, emails, credit cards —
        and replaces them with safe placeholders before forwarding to Anthropic.
      </p>

      <div class="diagram-flow glass">
        <div class="diagram-row">
          <div class="diagram-node">Claude Code</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-accent">Privacy Gateway</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-alt">Anthropic API</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-note">API keys, secrets, PII masked here → never reach Anthropic in plain text</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Setup Guide: Protect Claude Code in 30 Seconds</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Install the Gateway</h3>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Option A: Docker</div>
        <pre><code>docker run -d \
  --name ai-privacy-gw \
  -p 9999:9999 \
  -v ./vault_data:/app/vault_data \
  ghcr.io/gunxueqiu6/ai-privacy-gateway:lite</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Option B: Python (pip)</div>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/gunxueqiu6/ai-privacy-gateway
cd ai-privacy-gateway
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Step 2: Configure Claude Code</h3>
      <p>Set the <code>ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL</code> environment variable before launching Claude Code:</p>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">macOS / Linux</div>
        <pre><code>export ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9999/v1
claude</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Windows (PowerShell)</div>
        <pre><code>$env:ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL = "http://localhost:9999/v1"
claude</code></pre>
      </div>

      <p>Your existing <code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code> continues to work — the gateway forwards it automatically.</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Verify It Works</h3>
      <p>
        Ask Claude Code a question that references a file containing an API key or phone number.
        Open the gateway's admin dashboard at <a href="http://localhost:9999/admin">http://localhost:9999/admin</a>
        to see the masked entities in real time.
      </p>

      <h2>What Claude Code Users Are Masking</h2>
      <div class="entity-grid">
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-secret">API Keys</span> OpenAI, AWS, GitHub tokens in env and code</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-phone">Phone</span> Contact numbers in configuration files</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-email">Email</span> Developer emails, user emails in test data</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-id">ID Card</span> User identification numbers in data samples</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-bank">Bank</span> Payment processing code with test card numbers</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-name">Name</span> Employee names, customer names in code</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-loc">Address</span> Business addresses, customer locations</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-org">Secrets</span> Database URLs, passwords, connection strings</div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="seo-faq glass" id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does the gateway add latency to Claude Code?</h3>
          <p>No. The gateway adds under 1ms of average latency. P99 latency stays under 2ms. Claude Code's terminal experience remains unchanged.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Will this break Claude Code's context features?</h3>
          <p>No. The gateway only masks sensitive data patterns. All code context, file references, and conversation history pass through normally — just with sensitive data replaced by safe placeholders.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I use this with the Claude API directly?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Point any OpenAI-compatible or Anthropic-compatible client to <code>http://localhost:9999/v1</code>. The gateway works with any API that follows the chat completions format.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does it support streaming (SSE)?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The gateway fully supports SSE streaming with real-time masking and unmasking of response data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is it free for commercial use?</h3>
          <p>Yes. AI Privacy Gateway is MIT licensed. Free for personal and commercial use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="seo-cta">
        <h2>Protect Your Claude Code Sessions</h2>
        <p>Deploy AI Privacy Gateway in 30 seconds. Your data stays on your machine.</p>
        <div class="seo-cta-buttons">
          <a href="/download" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Free</a>
          <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Try the Demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Schema -->
      <script type="application/ld+json">{
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does the gateway add latency to Claude Code?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. The gateway adds under 1ms of average latency." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Will this break Claude Code's context features?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. The gateway only masks sensitive data patterns while preserving all context." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does it support streaming?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Full SSE streaming support with real-time masking and unmasking." } }
        ]
      }</script>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .seo-page { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; }
  .seo-page .container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .seo-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--primary);
    background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.15);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .seo-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .seo-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .seo-tldr {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .seo-tldr strong { color: var(--primary); }
  .seo-tldr code {
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  }

  .seo-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .seo-page h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .seo-page p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .seo-page ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .seo-page ul li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .seo-page ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.9rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .seo-page a { color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .seo-page a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .code-block { padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .code-block-title {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .code-block pre { margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: auto; }
  .code-block code { color: var(--primary); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

  .diagram-flow { padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .diagram-row {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .diagram-node {
    padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600;
    background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--primary);
  }
  .diagram-accent { color: var(--accent); background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.06); }
  .diagram-alt { color: var(--warning); background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.06); }
  .diagram-arrow { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .diagram-note { text-align: center; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic; }

  .entity-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .entity-item {
    display: flex; align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .entity-chip {
    font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .chip-secret { background: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.12); color: #f87171; }
  .chip-phone { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.12); color: #fbbf24; }
  .chip-email { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.12); color: #60a5fa; }
  .chip-id { background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.12); color: #86efac; }
  .chip-bank { background: rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.12); color: #f472b6; }
  .chip-name { background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.12); color: #a78bfa; }
  .chip-loc { background: rgba(252, 165, 165, 0.12); color: #fca5a5; }
  .chip-org { background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.12); color: #94a3b8; }

  .seo-faq { padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-faq h2 { border: none; margin-top: 0; }
  .faq-item { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item:last-child { border: none; }
  .faq-item h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .faq-item p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; }

  .seo-cta {
    text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background: var(--glass-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px; margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .seo-cta h2 { margin-top: 0; border: none; }
  .seo-cta p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .seo-page { padding: 6rem 0 3rem; }
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
    .entity-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .code-block pre { font-size: 0.75rem; }
    .diagram-row { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .seo-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .seo-cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
